Oyo State Government has threatened to sanction churches and mosques over noise pollution. The state government also urged residents of the state to comply with environmental regulations of the state, especially as it relates to noise pollution. The state Commissioner for Environment and Natural Resources, Hon. Kehinde Ayoola who stated this in Ibadan on Wednesday pointed out that noise pollution makes the environment unfriendly and as such creates severe influence on human mental and physical health. He enjoined residents to abide with regulations, calling for cooperation by residents of the state. Ayoola opined that failure to comply, might cause unending friction among parties involved, thereby causing conflict in the society. He noted that,’’ Adequate compliance would assist to foster better working relationship and conducive environment without confrontation and friction involving the parties. “Towards this end, the Oyo State government, through the Ministry has mandated all block industry owners, night clubs, patent medicine sellers, churches, mosques, musical vendors, street dancers to henceforth reduce their noise to permissible level that complies with existing law of the state. “Hesitation to abide by this law, the statement read, would attract heavy penalties and wrath of the binding laws of Oyo State”, he said. 